Items.Title: Resolution calling on the United States Congress to pass and the President to sign the Public Housing Equal Treatment Act of 2007 to allow for the full transition of 21 developments built by the City and State of New York into the Federal public housing program for funding purposes.
Items.ActionText: This Resolution was Hearing Held by Committee
Items.MatterName: Congress to pass and the President to sign the Public Housing Equal Treatment Act of 2007.
